for%20extreme%20brutality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BSignificant%20Operation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20second%20source%2C%20who%20also%20requested%20anonymity%20due%20to%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20the%20issue%2C%20said%20the%20information%20Tehran%20provided%20to%20Moscow%20about%20an%20impending%20attack%20had%20lacked%20specific%20details%20regarding%20timing%20and%20the%20exact%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20(the%20members%20of%20ISIS-K)%20were%20instructed%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20significant%20operation%20in%20Russia...%20One%20of%20the%20terrorists%20(arrested%20in%20Iran)%20said%20some%20members%20of%20the%20group%20had%20already%20travelled%20to%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20second%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20source%2C%20a%20senior%20security%20official%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20Iran%20has%20been%20a%20victim%20of%20terror%20attacks%20for%20years%2C%20Iranian%20authorities%20fulfilled%20their%20obligation%20to%20alert%20Moscow%20based%20on%20information%20acquired%20from%20those%20arrested%20terrorists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20Reuters%20report%2C%20Kremlin%20spokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20said%20on%20Monday%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20know%20anything%20about%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20foreign%20ministry%20did%20not%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20this%20story.%20The%20White%20House%20had%20no%20comment%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20familiar%20with%20the%20U.S.%20intelligence%20on%20an%20impending%20attack%20in%20Russia%20said%20it%20was%20based%20on%20interceptions%20of%20%26quot%3Bchatter%26quot%3B%20among%20ISIS-K%20militants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChallenging%20the%20U.S.%20assertions%2C%20Russia%20has%20said%20it%20believes%20Ukraine%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20attack%2C%20without%20providing%20evidence.%20Kyiv%20has%20strongly%20denied%20the%20assertion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3