ive%20behavior%20could%20be%20a%20game%20changer%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20curbing%20the%20unprecedented%20power%20of%20the%20tech%20giants.%20It%20offers%20regulators%20a%20way%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20monopoly-minded%20companies%20%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20try%20to%20buy%20up%20innovative%20young%20guns.%20%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20way%20of%20thinking%20about%20the%20threat%20to%20innovation%20from%20reduced%20competition%20has%20to%20do%20with%20market%20concentration%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20says.%20%26quot%3BNow%20we're%20taking%20it%20a%20little%20further.%20We're%20saying%2C%20by%20the%20time%20you%20get%20to%20an%20acquisition%20stage%2C%20that%20might%20be%20too%20late.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELemley%20and%20Wansley%20start%20their%20inquiry%20with%20a%20question%3A%20Why%20have%20two%20decades%20elapsed%20since%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20last%20massive%2C%20world-dominating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-ai-artificial-intelligence-how-to-prepare-history-productivity-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisruptive%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20tech%3F%20Apple%20and%20Microsoft%20were%20founded%20in%20the%20mid-1970s%3B%20Amazon%20and%20Google%20in%20the%201990s.%20Facebook%2C%20the%20baby%20of%20the%20bunch%2C%20was%20founded%20in%202004.%20The%20iPhone%20came%20out%20in%202007.%20What%20do%20we%20have%20to%20show%20for%20the%20past%2020%20years%20of%20venture%20capital%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20appears%20to%20be%3A%20just%20another%20industry%20that's%20terrified%20of%20competition.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20Big%20Tech%20looks%20at%20promising%20startups%20the%20way%20evil%20alien%20empires%20in%20science%20fiction%20look%20at%20helpless%20planets.%20Sometimes%20they%20act%20like%20the%20Borg%20from%20Star%20Trek%2C%20assimilating%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiological%20and%20technological%20distinctiveness%26quot%3B%20of%20competitors%20to%20make%20themselves%20more%20badass.%20Here%20on%2