n%20would%20be%2C%20well%2C%20disruptive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20something%20that%20people%20write%20about%20or%20talk%20about%2C%20not%20something%20that%20surfaces%20regularly%2C%26quot%3B%20Lemley%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20in%20the%20air%20if%20you're%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20talking%20to%20venture%20capitalists.%20It's%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20bigger%20the%20company%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20financial%20risk%20of%20any%20disruption%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20small.%20Like%20an%20evil%20king%20facing%20a%20prophecy%20that%20he%20will%20one%20day%20be%20overthrown%20by%20a%20firstborn%20child%20from%20the%20forest%20realm%2C%20the%20company%20has%20to%20kill%20%3Cem%3Eall%20t%3C%2Fem%3Ehe%20children%2C%20just%20to%20be%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20on%20a%20stage%20%E2%80%94%20Sam%20Altman%20of%20OpenAI%20and%20Satya%20Nadella%20of%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20with%20their%20corporate%20logos%20in%20the%20background%2C%20the%20OpenAI%20knott%20and%20MSFT's%20quad-colored%20squares%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6604990d16bde8d4ead2da13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%20(left)%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20with%20Satya%20Nadella%20of%20Microsoft.%20The%20tech%20giant%20owns%2048%25%20of%20the%20startup%2C%20and%20has%20a%20seat%20on%20its%20board.%20%3Cp%3EBarbara%20Ortutay%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%2C%20mass%20murders%20of%20forest-realm%20firstborns%20tend%20to%20attract%20the%20attention%20of%20regulators.%20So%20what%20if%20the%20evil%20king%20just%20%3Cem%3Eadopted%3C%2Fem%3E%20all%20the%20babies%3F%20Raise%20them%20rich%20and%20spoiled%20in%20the%20castle%2C%20distract%20them%20with%20nubile%20romantic%20prospects%2C%20teach%20them%20to%20exploit%20the%20peasants%3F%20Between%20assimilation%20or%20assassination%20lies%20%26quot%3Ba%20third%20possibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20the%20acquirer%20is%20going%20to%20take%20the%20startup%20and%20totally%20shut%20the%20technology%20down.%20It's%20that%20they%20will%20redirect%20the%20assets%20to%20something%20more%20profitable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20the%20tech%20giants%20are%20doing.%20How%3F%20First%2C%20by%20relying%20on%20Silicon%20Valley's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fventure-capital-big-tech-antitrust-predatory-pricing-uber-wework-bird-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetwork%20of%20venture%20capitalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20early-warning%20system%20for%20would-be%20disruptors.%20VCs%20see%20trends%20and%20startups%20that%20might%20someday%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20established%20order%20%E2%80%94%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarship.law.upenn.edu%2Fpenn_law_review%2Fvol168%2Fiss7%2F1%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enascent%20competitors%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20before%20anyone%20else.%20And%20there's%20nothing%20stopping%20them.%20As%20Lemley%20observes%2C%20it's%20part%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20%26quot%3Bnatural%20information%20flow%26quot%3B%20for%20an%20investor%20to%20tell%20a%20Google%20or%20a%20Microsoft%20about%20the%20promising%20newcomers%20they're%20backing.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20a%20VC%2C%20how%20am%20I%20going%20to%20get%20the%20best%20deal%20for%20my%20client%20in%20this%20space%3F%26quot%3B%20Lemley%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20deal%20might%20be%2C%20sell%20out%20to%20the%20incumbent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20tech%20giant%20gets%20a%20tip-off%20about%20a%20startup%20that%20might%20threaten%20their%20bottom%20line%2C%20they're%20able%20to%20strategically%20invest%20their%20vast%20cash%20reserves%20in%20the%20fledgling%20firm.%20That's%20precisely%20what's%20taking%20place%20with%20artificial%20intelligence%3A%20Microsoft%20owns%2048%25%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20emerging%20field's%20undisputed%20leader.%20Alphabet%20and%20Amazon%20have%20put%20billions%20of%20dollars%20into%20the%20AI%20startup%20Anthropic.%20When%20the%20two%20AI%20companies%20were%20founded%2C%20Wansley%20says%2C%20both%20were%20%26quot%3Bworried%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20one%20of%20the%20tech%20giants%20started%20looking%20in%20their%20direction.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20both%20are%20directly%20influenced%20by%20the%20very%20companies%20they%20set%20out%20to%20disrupt.%20And%20since%20investments%20from%20Big%20Tech%20often%20come%20with%20a%20seat%20on%20a%20startup's%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20Wansley%20adds%2C%20the%20tech%20giants%20are%20in%20an%20ideal%20position%20to%20%26quot%3Bstart%20nudging%20the%20company%20in%20a%20direction%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20less%20competitive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoney%20isn't%20the%20only%20weapon%20that%20Big%20Tech%20can%20deploy%20to%20co-opt%20a%20potential%20competitor.%20Because%20the%20tech%20giants%20have%20amassed%20huge%20repositories%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ford-gm-volvo-supercharger-electric-cars-charger-network-data-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20on%20user%20behavior%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20can%20choose%20with%20whom%20they%20share%20that%20data%2C%20and%20how%20much.%20Documents%20leaked%20from%20the%20discovery%20phase%20of%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20Facebook%20in%202015%20showed%20that%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Ftech%2Fsocial-media%2Fmark-zuckerberg-leveraged-facebook-user-%2520data-fight-rivals-help-friends-n994706%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edoled%20out%20data%20access%20preferentially%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20its%20allies%20more%20access%20than%20its%20potential%20competitors.%20The%20data%20that%20Big%20Tech%20shares%20%E2%80%94%20or%20doesn't%20share%20%E2%80%94%20can%20play%20an%20instrumental%20role%20in%20shaping%20a%20startup's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20big%20companies%20use%20their%20clout%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20impose%20stricter%20regulations%20on%20the%20startups%20they're%20ostensibly%20trying%20to%20help.%20That's%20why%20tech%20giants%20like%20Meta%20testify%20before%20congressional%20hearings%20and%20ask%20for%20more%20government%20oversight%20for%20emerging%20threats%20like%20robot%20cars%2C%20or%20AI.%20They%20want%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20rules%20favor%20them%20%E2%80%94%20and%20disfavor%20startups%20outside%20their%20zone%20of%20protection.%20Big%20Tech%20may%20hate%20regulation%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20mind%20using%20it%20to%20regulate%20any%20startups%20that%20might%20wind%20up%20threatening%20its%20dominance%20in%20the%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECo-opting%20startups%20is%20a%20clever%20strategy.%20It's%20way%20easier%20%E2%80%94%20and%20less%20obvious%20%E2%80%94%20than%20buying%20up%20a%20competitor%20and%20shutting%20it%20down.%20And%20if%20it%20doesn't%20work%2C%20the%20nuclear%20option%20is%20always%20available.%20%26quot%3BIf%20all%20those%20other%20strategies%20fail%20%E2%80%94%20investments%2C%20taking%20a%20seat%20on%20the%20board%2C%20playing%20hardball%20with%20data%20networks%2C%20and%20regulation%20%E2%80%94%20if%20none%20of%20them%20prevents%20a%20competitor%20from%20growing%2C%20then%20the%20tech%20companies%20can%20buy%20it%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Wansley%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20little%20subtle%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20what%20makes%20it%20so%20effective.%20Straight-up%20killer%20acquisitions%20are%20relatively%20easy%20to%20prove%2C%20says%20Florian%20Ederer%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Boston%20University.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20much%2C%20much%20harder%20to%20prove%20that%20a%20company%20got%20taken%20over%20and%20its%20focus%20got%20slightly%20shifted%20to%20not%20competing%20quite%20so%20intensely.%26quot%3B%20It's%20even%20harder%20to%20prove%20that%20consumers%20suffered%20any%20ill%20effects.%20The%20co-opted%20companies%20don't%20get%20killed%20off%2C%20and%20they%20stay%20nominally%20independent.%20The%20founders%20and%20investors%20get%20rich%20either%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20do%20we%20know%20startups%20are%20getting%20co-opted%20by%20Big%20Tech%3F%20One%20proof%20is%20that%20some%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20most%20powerful%20players%20are%20starting%20to%20grouse%20about%20it.%20Elon%20Musk%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F02%2Ftechnology%2Felon-musk-openai-lawsuit-paradox.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esuing%20OpenAI%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20the%20company%20from%20sharing%20its%20tech%20with%20Microsoft.%20The%20venture%20capitalist%20Marc%20Andreessen%20tweeted%20last%20month%20that%20Big%20Tech%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BNew%20Incumbents%26quot%3B%20in%20AI%20are%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fpmarca%2Fstatus%2F1762532979317043515%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elobbying%20as%20a%20group%20with%20great%20intensity%20to%20establish%20a%20government%20protected%20cartel%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20You%20know%20things%20are%20bad%20when%20the%20biggest%20kids%20on%20the%20block%20start%20whining%20about%20being%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWansley%20and%20Lemley%20argue%20that%20regulators%20need%20to%20step%20in%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20restrain%20competition%2C%20but%20to%20unleash%20it.%20For%20starters%2C%20they%20say%2C%20the%20feds%20should%20strengthen%20and%20enforce%20existing%20rules%20against%20%26quot%3Binterlocking%20directorates%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20are%20supposed%20to%20prevent%20executives%20from%20sitting%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20their%20competitors.%20In%20the%202000s%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Google%20was%20on%20Apple's%20board!%20These%20days%20that%20kind%20of%20thing%20gives%20the%20feds%20a%20frowny%20face%3B%20in%202022%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20pushed%20seven%20directors%20representing%20venture%20firms%20to%20resign%20from%20the%20boards%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-says-seven-board-directors-resigned-under-antitrust-pressure-2022-10-19%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efive%20of%20their%20direct%20competitors%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20space%2C%20edtech%2C%20and%20green%20energy.%20Microsoft%20currently%20enjoys%20a%20seat%20on%20OpenAI's%20board%20of%20directors.%20Technically%20it's%20only%20an%20observer%20role%2C%20without%20a%20vote.%20But%2C%20come%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20goal%20of%20the%20scholars%20I%20spoke%20with%20is%20broader%20than%20any%20specific%20regulation%3A%20They%20just%20want%20to%20get%20government%20watchdogs%20to%20recognize%20the%20new%20and%20subtle%20ways%20that%20tech%20giants%20are%20shutting%20down%20competition%20and%20innovation.%20Sure%2C%20people%20are%20still%20founding%20tech%20companies%2C%20and%20their%20startups%20are%20still%20getting%20funded.%20But%20more%20and%20more%2C%20they're%20basically%20serving%20as%20farm%20teams%20for%20the%20majors.%20%26quot%3BThe%20incumbents%20have%20gotten%20much%20more%20attuned%20to%20competitive%20pressures%20from%20nascent%20competitors%2C%20and%20address%20them%20more%20aggressively%20and%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20Ederer%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%2C%20for%20their%20part%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20catching%20on.%20In%20late%20January%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20ordered%20three%20titans%20of%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Alphabet%20%E2%80%94%20to%20open%20the%20books%20on%20their%20investments%20in%20artificial%20intelligence.%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%20received%20the%20same%20letter%3A%20Send%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fftc-to-look-into-tech-giants-ai-partnerships-1033002313%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eevery%20scrap%20of%20documenta